narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend the class to other students if it is not as a 5th class. The class itself was very interesting and engaging and there were no midterms or final exams, but there was a lot of work and reading every week. It was challenging to balance this course if you are also taking 4 other classes. However, the professor is great and engaging and the material is fun to learn and highly applicable to real life.
Super easy, not a lot of work, interesting readings.
It's an interesting course, but you will be learning mostly about water in relation to geophysics (other plants) rather than geology (finding water on earth.)
